    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Rounded vessels that are generally wider than they are high, usually hemispherical or nearly so. A bowl may have a spreading base or foot ring and sometimes two handles or a cover. Distinguished from a cup, which is rather deep than wide.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
